 {"id":"bd-1n5t","title":"Focus Management System: Keyboard Navigation Graph","description":"## Background

FrankenTUI currently has bd-3vbf.25 (Focus Management: Visual Focus States) which covers the *visual* aspect of focus. However, there's no system for:

- Managing focus order (Tab/Shift-Tab navigation)
- Focus trapping (for modals/dialogs)
- Focus restoration (returning to previous focus after modal closes)
- Programmatic focus control
- Skip links and focus shortcuts

Without this, keyboard-only users cannot effectively navigate complex UIs, and modals cannot properly trap focus.

## Problem Statement

Consider a UI with:
- Sidebar (focusable)
- Main content with form fields
- Help overlay (modal)

Current behavior:
- Tab goes... somewhere? No defined order
- Opening help doesn't trap focus
- Closing help doesn't restore focus
- No way to skip to main content

## Solution: Focus Management System

A FocusManager in ftui-runtime that:
1. Maintains a focus graph (not just linear order)
2. Handles Tab/Shift-Tab navigation
3. Supports focus trapping for modals
4. Provides focus restoration
5. Integrates with Semantic Events (#1) for proper event routing

## Proposed API

```rust
/// Unique identifier for focusable elements
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub struct FocusId(u64);

/// Focus group for modals and regions
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct FocusTrap {
    pub id: FocusTrapId,
    pub focusables: Vec<FocusId>,
    pub initial_focus: Option<FocusId>,
    pub restore_on_exit: bool,
}

/// Main focus manager
pub struct FocusManager {
    /// All registered focusables in document order
    focus_order: Vec<FocusId>,
    /// Current focus
    current: Option<FocusId>,
    /// Stack of focus traps (modals)
    trap_stack: Vec<FocusTrap>,
    /// History for restoration
    history: Vec<FocusId>,
}

impl FocusManager {
    pub fn register(&mut self, id: FocusId, after: Option<FocusId>);
    pub fn unregister(&mut self, id: FocusId);
    pub fn focus(&mut self, id: FocusId) -> bool;
    pub fn focus_next(&mut self) -> Option<FocusId>;
    pub fn focus_prev(&mut self) -> Option<FocusId>;
    pub fn focus_first(&mut self) -> Option<FocusId>;
    pub fn focus_last(&mut self) -> Option<FocusId>;
    pub fn current(&self) -> Option<FocusId>;

    // Trapping
    pub fn push_trap(&mut self, trap: FocusTrap);
    pub fn pop_trap(&mut self) -> Option<FocusId>; // Returns restored focus

    // Query
    pub fn is_focused(&self, id: FocusId) -> bool;
    pub fn is_in_trap(&self, id: FocusId) -> bool;
}

/// Trait for focusable widgets
pub trait Focusable {
    fn focus_id(&self) -> FocusId;
    fn can_focus(&self) -> bool { true }
    fn on_focus(&mut self) {}
    fn on_blur(&mut self) {}
    fn focus_style(&self) -> Option<Style> { None }
}
```

## Integration Points

1. **Program**: Auto-handle Tab/Shift-Tab
2. **Frame**: Track focused widget for rendering
3. **Widgets**: Implement Focusable trait
4. **Modal System**: Use focus traps

## Benefits

- Consistent keyboard navigation
- Proper modal behavior
- Accessibility compliance
- Better UX for power users

## Files to Create/Modify

- crates/ftui-core/src/focus.rs (NEW)
- crates/ftui-runtime/src/focus_manager.rs (NEW)
- crates/ftui-runtime/src/program.rs (integrate)
- crates/ftui-widgets/src/lib.rs (Focusable trait)

## Success Criteria
- Epic delivers a cohesive user-visible capability: Focus Management System: Keyboard Navigation Graph
- Child tasks are not just implemented; each has unit tests + E2E scripts with verbose JSONL logs and deterministic fixtures
- Graceful degradation tiers are specified (capabilities, fallbacks, safety) and validated in tests
